  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">Congratulations on completing week eight! After finishing your lessons you should now know:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">9 new kanji</span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">12 new words in katakana</span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Counting up to 1 billion</span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">How to express\"to go do something... and then come back\" using the<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"> てform ＋きます</span></span> </span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">How to express\"to become\" using になります</span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">How to express\"to put on/to take off clothes\" using the てform+います</span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">How to report/quote something that was said using と言いました</span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">How to use a plain style in informal conversations</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">How to use らforms and to use the expressions よかったらand またこんど</span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">How to use 〜てもform and 〜なくてもform</span></li>\n<li>\n<span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">How to use 5 new grammar points:</span><ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">Grammar focus on これから</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">Grammar focus on new uses of が, の and も</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">Grammar focus on the particles に, と and を</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">Gramma<span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">r focus on もし for\"if\"</span></span></li>\n<li>\n<span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">Gramma</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\">r focus on に as a substitute of へ</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">If you have any questions on what you have learned this week, don’t forget that you can always ask for more help in the student community!</span></span><br></span></p>\n</div><p><a href=\"https://japaneseonline.gogonihon.com/communities/Q29tbXVuaXR5LTM1MzQ=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/ca7/9fe/ff2/Go_to_community_%281%29.png\" style=\"width: 300px;\" class=\"fr-fic fr-dib\" srcset=\"https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/ca7/9fe/ff2/Go_to_community_%281%29.png?width=1920 1x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/ca7/9fe/ff2/Go_to_community_%281%29.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=2 2x, https://files.cdn.thinkific.com/file_uploads/259518/images/ca7/9fe/ff2/Go_to_community_%281%29.png?width=1920&amp;dpr=3 3x\"></a></p>",
